\begin_layout Standard
Since by definition 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{i\in Contributors_{a}}\frac{q_{ai}}{Q_{a}}=1$
\end_inset

 , we can deduce from the fact that 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{-\epsilon_{u_{i}'}^{a}}{\epsilon_{h_{i,a}'}}\geq-1\forall i\in Contributors_{a}$
\end_inset

 that the denominator, 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{1}\text{+\text{\ensuremath{\sum_{i\in Contributors_{a}(0)}\frac{q_{i,a}}{Q_{a}}\frac{-\epsilon_{u_{i}'}^{a}}{\epsilon_{h_{i,a}'}}}}}$
\end_inset

, is positive.
 Let us from now on focus on the generic case in which this is strictly
 positive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now consider the expression 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\sum_{b\neq a}\frac{Q_{b}}{Q-Q_{a}}\frac{\partial u_{i}}{\partial Q_{b}}}{\frac{\partial u_{i}}{\partial Q_{a}}}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i\in Contributor_{a}$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{b\neq a}\frac{Q_{b}}{Q-Q_{a}}=1,$
\end_inset

